Hybrids are just fine. The Melee classes are the ones that are screwed up (Warrior-Monk-Rogue). Rangers and Rogues own DPS over Warriors..but wear Chain and have far fewer HPs. Monks are the sh*t when it comes to avoidance (which is a game design flaw). Knights are close to Warriors but do less damage. And they Do have less Hps. Not as less as a Bard-Rngr-Rogue, but less. And the object of the game is to do damage to the mob &amp; kill it (raid or xp grp) before it kills you. Currently, Warriors &gt; All for Hps. It shouldn't be too hard to code some Mobs to have thier own damage tables relative to AC (damage mitigation). Some zones like CT-Deep-Acrylia Cavs are very Warrior-friendly. Other places, its fine to have a Knight or Rngr to MA for Xp. Never should a Monk MA, regardless of thier mitigation. Lack of any triggerable agro is what disqualifies them. As an example, take a lvl 51 Shammy into Pit Spiders in Velks. I would rather have a Ranger or Knight MA to keep the resist agro null and void. But that is an exception, the rule is generally to get a Warrior and appropriate levels around them. *Note: If any of you wish to quote anymore, post the whole quote...stop taking sh*t out of context*<br>
<br>
Now, to get back to the original theme of this thread: I see no reason for Offense/Defense upgrades to Warriors. (/duck) What I DO see a need for is some utility based in the offensive/defensive realms. Don't want to have Warriors replacing any other classes, as no other classes are replacing them (contrary to popular belief). Some long duration Stuns/short duration Debuffs could be some cool skills under offense. Some improvements vs certain weapon types (higher mitigation or avoidance vs 1hb, 1hp, ect..buy em in AA) could be some cool defensive skills to implement. Try to think of something besides just jacking up the scale of a game that is currently f*cked up. All you would get then is a game thats f*cked up with higher numbers.<br>
<br>
No More Pally Vs. Warrior crap! Get this thread back on track peeps...<br>
