<br>
On raids :<br>
- The only advantage to warriors over other tanks is 2 disciplines : Evasive, and Defensive. Their duration is about 3min. On Luclin mobs, 3min mean nothing.<br>
- I'm curious to know how many warriors are MT's so they have to use defensive/evasive, and how many are only damages dealers, so they have *NOTHING*. I am lucky : I am MT.<br>
- With godly weapons (for instance, the 1HB 40 damage, 35 delay, from Grieg's End, easy to get for a non-Vindi capable guild !), damage output for paladins (I don't know well for SKs) is almost... or maybe more than warriors one. *with equal difficulty gear* (try to list warriors' only weapons dropped on mobs that are on the same difficulty than for paladins' one, and take a good laugh).<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong. I don't want damage increase. I don't want nerfs on other classes. I don't want to be able to solo some dragon.<br>
I only want to do my job : to be the meat shield and actually to have tools to assume this role.<br>
And I want to be UNIQUE. I *WANT* to have something, even if not really useful (like criticals before AA), that makes a warrior not only an ersatz of a paladin/sk.<br>
