And don't put words in my mouth, or attribute greed to ME.  I NEVER said that warriors should be irreplaceable, just the logical choice when it comes to Melee tanking, the first choice, the best.  It's all we do.<br>
<br>
Your little points spread inlcuded only 1-2 things that were really valid, the rest were nothing but stretches... Broader choices?  WTF is that supposed to mean?  That we can have MORE stuff that's inferior to yours and we're supposed to be happy?<br>
<br>
The &quot;Spell Effects on Gear&quot; argument is about the most pathetic I've seen.  If having spells on gear that you're not supposed to naturally have is a big issue, how come so many Paladins camp Stormfeather?  The ONLY spell effect which we have on gear which you don't is Invis, but guess what...that's now covered too.  You don't believe in weapons procs, or gear effects?  You never used a DW helm?  Eyepatch of Plunder?  Monks can't summon 100% weight reduction bags full of throwing hammers?  Warriors are one class who gets spell effects on armor, AS EVERY OTHER F*ING CLASS ALSO DOES.<br>
<br>
Newsflsh...Triple attack is nothing, period, it's nothing.  It's a proc, like any other proc, it's entirely unreliable, and rarely does it have any substantive meaning.<br>
<br>
Your only credible points were &quot;key Parts of raids&quot; and &quot;Higher Caps&quot;... I left those out.  The rest are nothing but intellectual gymnastics.   Now, I'll agree that I didnt' put those in my list, so put em in there.  Do you STILL think that that is &quot;balanced&quot; with your spells/skills?  <br>
<br>
Oh, and throw out any disc other than Defensive and Evasive because they're all garbage, and meaningless.<br>
